Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.sort.generic

Interface Sort<X>

Type Parameters:
X - the type of the elements to be sorted.
All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable
All Known Subinterfaces:
ProcessingSort<X>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BubbleSort, BucketSort, ClassicSort, ClassificationSorter, GenericSortWithHelper, HeapSort, InsertionSort, InsertionSortComparator, InsertionSortOpt, IntroSort, LSDStringSort, MergeSort, MergeSortBasic, MSDStringSort, QuickSort, QuickSort_3way, QuickSort_Basic, QuickSort_DualPivot, QuickSort_Exp, RandomSort, SelectionSort, ShellSort, SortWithComparableHelper, SortWithHelper, SortWithHelperAndAdditionalMemory, TimSort
public interface Sort<X> extends AutoCloseable
Interface Sort which defines the various sort methods for sorting elements of type X. NOTE this definition does not assume that X extends Comparable of X.

    • sort

      default X[] sort(X[] xs, boolean makeCopy)
      Generic, non-mutating sort method which allows for explicit determination of the makeCopy option.
      Parameters:
      xs - sort the array xs, returning the sorted result, leaving xs unchanged.
      makeCopy - if set to true, we make a copy first and sort that.

    • sort

    • mutatingSort

      default void mutatingSort(X[] xs)
      Generic, mutating sort method. Note that there is no return value.
      Parameters:
      xs - the array to be sorted.

    • sort

      void sort(X[] xs, int from, int to)
      Generic, mutating sort method which operates on a sub-array.
      Parameters:
      xs - sort the array xs from "from" until "to" (exclusive of to).
      from - the index of the first element to sort.
      to - the index of the first element not to sort.

    • sort

      default Iterable<X> sort(Collection<X> xs)
      Method to take a Collection of X and return an Iterable of X in order.
      Parameters:
      xs - the collection of X elements.
      Returns:
      a sorted iterable of X.
